about

06:39.921 --> 06:52.375
the advance in the technology here. And I think in 
some ways the early days were a little bit like this

06:52.945 --> 07:04.921
skipper trying to get to the iceberg.

07:08.926 --> 07:15.174
So we've come a long ways in that respect. Was there 
any single amazing discovery in oceanography

07:15.194 --> 07:21.282
that seemed to amaze you the most? in your career, 
anything that took you simply off balance?

07:30.765 --> 07:37.933
I don't think that I was built to be caught too much 
by surprise.

07:41.196 --> 07:49.885
There's been a lot of things that I've really 
appreciated that's come along, and the great

07:41.196 --> 07:49.885
developments and strides that have been been made 
here. But I think a lot of the sort of big strides

07:52.249 --> 08:06.389
have been from a certain amount of group effort. 
And of course, with the increasing number of

08:07.871 --> 08:15.602
people, you don't see the ones that particularly 
stand out head and shoulders above all others.

08:22.230 --> 08:37.473
